    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Find an appropriate place to set these parameters.\r\n\r\n* `evm.constants` - module is getting a bit full but a fine default location to start with.\r\n* `evm.vm.forks.sharding.constants` - where the rest of the sharding code lives.\r\n* `evm.sharding.constants` - assumes creation of a new `evm.sharding` module which might be appropriate.\r\n\r\nAlso, if these values need to be configurable and not *true* constants, I would propose making them configurable using environment variables.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nLOOKAHEAD_PERIODS = int(os.environ.get('PYEVM_SHARDING_LOOKAHEAD_PERIODS', 4))\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis pattern is fine, however, it will execute once at module load and be done.  I'd suggest something more akin to this so that it can be changed at runtime.\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef get_sharding_config():\r\n    return {\r\n        'LOOKAHEAD_PERIODS': int(os.environ.get('PYEVM_SHARDING_LOOKAHEAD_PERIODS', 4)),\r\n        ...\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis way anything that needs these constants, or to modify them at runtime can do so.\r\n  ",
